{"title_page": "Cherish the Day", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2011}}\n{{Use British English|date=December 2011}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Cherish the Day\n| cover      = Sade - Cherish the Day.png\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Sade (band)|Sade]]\n| album      = [[Love Deluxe]]\n| released   = {{Start date|1993|7|17|df=yes}}\n| format     =\n* [[CD single|CD]]\n* [[12-inch single|12-inch]]\n* [[Cassette single|cassette]]\n| recorded   = 1992\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Trip hop]]<ref>{{cite web |last=Kellman |first=Andy |url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/sade-mn0000279337/biography |title=Sade {{!}} Biography & History |website=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=28 December 2019}}</ref>\n| length     = 5:34\n| label      = [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n| writer     = \n* [[Sade (singer)|Sade Adu]]\n* Andrew Hale\n* [[Stuart Matthewman]]\n| producer   =\n* Sade\n* [[Mike Pela]] ({{abbr|co.|co-producer}})\n| prev_title = [[Kiss of Life (Sade song)|Kiss of Life]]\n| prev_year  = 1993\n| next_title = [[By Your Side (Sade song)|By Your Side]]\n| next_year  = 2000\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|pKhfoKOTwZY|\"Cherish the Day\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Cherish the Day'''\" is a song by English band [[Sade (band)|Sade]] from their fourth studio album, ''[[Love Deluxe]]'' (1992). It was released as the album's fourth and final single in the United Kingdom on 17 July 1993 and in the United States on 11 September 1993. \n\n==Reception==\n''[[Music & Media]]'' wrote, \"Despite the artwork, showing Sade with a guitar and a stack of speakers in the background, she hasn't rocked up her sound. On the contrary, with a lonely drum track on a synth carpet, \"ambient soul\" is within reach.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/UK/Music-and-Media/90s/1993/MM-1993-08-07.pdf|title=New Releases: Singles|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|volume=10|issue=32|page=7|date=7 August 1993|accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref> Tanya Rena Jefferson of [[AXS (company)|AXS]] stated, \"This joyous soulful song embraces one to cherish each and every day.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Jefferson |first=Tanya Rena |url=https://www.axs.com/sade-s-10-best-songs-47376 |title=Sade's 10 best songs |website=[[AXS (company)|AXS]] |date=2 April 2015 |accessdate=21 June 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160426130707/http://www.axs.com/sade-s-10-best-songs-47376 |archivedate=26 April 2016}}</ref> Sophie Heawood of ''[[The Guardian]]'' commented \"The band at their most abstractly evocative: at their best, they could do a remarkable amount with very little \u2013 as proved by this song, during which immense yearning is conveyed.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Heawood |first=Sophie |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/mar/13/why-sade-bigger-adele-us |title=Why Sade is bigger in the US than Adele |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=13 March 2012 |accessdate=21 June 2019}}</ref> Frank Guan of [[Vulture (blog)|Vulture]] added, \"Her minimalist lyrics... say all that needs to be said, and once a ten-note bassline jumps in to underscore her depth of feeling over the misty synths, the song is perfect and complete.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Guan |first=Frank |url=https://www.vulture.com/2017/10/all-73-sade-songs-ranked-from-worst-to-best.html |title=All 73 Sade Songs, Ranked From Worst to Best |website=[[Vulture (blog)|Vulture]] |date=26 October 2017 |accessdate=21 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\nFilmed in black and white by Derek M. Allen, the music video for \"Cherish the Day\" features [[Sade (singer)|Sade Adu]] performing the song whilst playing the guitar on the rooftop of a New York City skyscraper as her bandmates and a few other people vibe to the music on the streets below.\n\n==Track listings==\n*'''UK, European and Japanese CD single'''\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix short version) \u2013 5:18\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix long version) \u2013 6:18\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Ronin remix) \u2013 6:58\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Pal Joey remix) \u2013 6:46\n\n*'''US CD single'''\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix) \u2013 6:18\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Ronin remix) \u2013 6:58\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Pal Joey remix) \u2013 6:46\n#\"[[Feel No Pain]]\" ([[Nellee Hooper]] remix) \u2013 5:09\n#\"[[No Ordinary Love]]\" (album version) \u2013 7:18\n\n*'''Australian CD single / US cassette single'''\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix) \u2013 6:18\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Ronin remix) \u2013 6:58\n#\"Cherish the Day\" (Pal Joey remix) \u2013 6:46\n\n*'''UK and Dutch 12-inch single'''\n:A1. \"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix long version) \u2013 6:18\n:A2. \"Cherish the Day\" (Ronin remix) \u2013 6:58\n:B1. \"Cherish the Day\" (Pal Joey remix) \u2013 6:46\n:B2. \"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix short version) \u2013 5:18\n\n*'''US limited-edition 12-inch single'''\n:A1. \"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix long version) \u2013 6:18\n:A2. \"Cherish the Day\" (Ronin remix) \u2013 6:58\n:B1. \"Cherish the Day\" (Pal Joey remix) \u2013 6:46\n:B2. \"Feel No Pain\" (Nellee Hooper remix) \u2013 5:09\n:B3. \"No Ordinary Love\" (album edit) \u2013 5:23\n\n*'''US 7-inch single'''\n:A1. \"Cherish the Day\" (Sade remix short version) \u2013 5:18\n:A2. \"Cherish the Day\" (Ronin remix) \u2013 6:58\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (1993)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br>position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref>{{cite web |url=https://i.imgur.com/NqdaJXC.jpg |title=Response from ARIA re: Sade ARIA singles chart history, received 19 September 2017 |accessdate=19 September 2017 |via=[[Imgur]]}}</ref>\n| 207\n|-\n{{single chart|UKsinglesbyname|53|artist=Sade|artistid=21427|rowheader=true|accessdate=19 September 2017}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Billboardbubbling100|16|artist=Sade|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 December 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Hot Dance Singles Sales]] (''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'')<ref>{{cite 