{"title_page": "Hukou, Hsinchu", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Kouhu}}\n{{coord|24|54|N|121|03|E|display=title|region:TW_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n{{Short description|rural township of Hsinchu County, Taiwan}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->| official_name                   = Hukou Township<br>\u6e56\u53e3\u9115\n| nickname                        = \n| motto                           = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Township (Taiwan)|Rural township]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_flag                      = File:Emblem of hukou township.png\n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = Sj hk.png\n| map_caption                     = Hukou Township in Hsinchu County\n| subdivision_type                = Location\n| subdivision_type1               = \n| subdivision_name                = [[Hsinchu County]], [[Taiwan]]\n| subdivision_name1               = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| established_title2              = \n| established_date2               = \n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = \n| area_total_km2                  = 58.4303\n| area_land_sq_mi                 = \n| area_land_km2                   = \n| area_water_sq_mi                = \n| area_water_km2                  = \n| area_urban_sq_mi                = \n| area_urban_km2                  = \n| area_metro_km2                  = \n| area_metro_sq_mi                = \n| population_as_of                = July 2018\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_total                = 77567\n| population_urban                = \n| population_metro                = \n| population_density_sq_mi        = \n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| timezone                        = \n| utc_offset                      = \n| timezone_DST                    = \n| utc_offset_DST                  = \n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| elevation_m                     = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| name                            = \n}}\n[[File:\u6e56\u53e3\u9109\u516c\u6240 Hukou Township Government - panoramio.jpg|thumb|Hukou Township Office]]\n\n'''Hukou Township''' ({{zh|t=\u6e56\u53e3\u9115|p=H\u00fak\u01d2u Xi\u0101ng}}) is a [[Township (Taiwan)|rural township]] of [[Hsinchu County]], [[Taiwan]]. With an area of {{convert|58.43|km2|abbr=on}}, it is the third largest township in the county. Hukou had an estimated population of 77,908 in December 2019.<ref>{{cite web\n | url =http://w3.hsinchu.gov.tw/house/print/city.aspx?y=106&m=1\n | script-title =zh:106\u5e741\u6708 \u65b0\u7af9\u7e23\u4eba\u53e3\u7d71\u8a08\u5831\u8868\n | trans-title =Hsinchu County population table, January 2017\n | language=zh\n | website =hsinchu.gov.tw\n | publisher =Hsinchu County Gov't\n | access-date = 14 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe Hukou army base houses the 542nd Armor Brigade of the 6th Army Corps of the [[Republic of China Army]].\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nThe township comprises 20 villages: Aishi, Boluo, Decheng, Fenghuang, Fengshan, Hexing, Hujing, Hukou, Hunan, Renshi, Shengli, Tungxing, Xiaoshi, Xinshi, Xinyi, Zhangan, Zhangling, Zhongshi, Zhongxing and Zhongzheng.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://vote2014.nat.gov.tw/en/TV/nm701000500000000.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-12-09 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20141209105554/http://vote2014.nat.gov.tw/en/TV/nm701000500000000.html |archive-date=2014-12-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Economy==\nThe township is home to the [[Hsinchu Industrial Park]].\n\n==Education==\n\n*[[China University of Technology]], Hsinchu campus\n*Hsinchu county Hukou senior high school, incl. grades 7 to 9\n*Hsinchu county Xinhu junior high school\n*Hsinchu county Chungcheng junior high school\n*Hsinchu county Hukou elementary school\n*Hsinchu county Changan elementary school\n*Hsinchu county Xinshih elementary school\n*Hsinchu county Xinhu elementary school\n*Hsinchu county Chungxing elementary school\n*Hsinchu county Hexing elementary school\n*Hsinchu county Huaxing elementary school\n\n{{Infobox Chinese\n| c = {{linktext|\u6e56\u53e3|\u9109}}\n| t = \u6e56\u53e3\u9109\n| s = \n| p = H\u00fak\u01d2u Xi\u0101ng\n| j = hu1 kou3 xiang1\n| mi = {{IPAc-cmn|h|u|2|.|k|ou|3|-|shi|ang|1}}\n| ci = \n| altname = [[Chinese name#Milk|Hukou Township]]\n| bpmf = \u310f\u3128\u02ca&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\u310e\u3121\u02c7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\u3112\u3127\u3124\n| title = Hukou Township\n}}\n\n==Tourist attractions==\n* [[Armor School Museum]]\n*[[Hukou Old Street]]\n*Sanyuan Temple of Laohukou<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hchcc.gov.tw/ch/06culture/cul_02_main.asp?bull_id=1067|title=Sanyuan Temple of Laohukou|last=|first=|date=|website=\u65b0\u7af9\u7e23\u6587\u5316\u5c40|access-date=}}</ref>\n*Catholic Church of Laohukou <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hchcc.gov.tw/ch/06culture/cul_02_main.asp?bull_id=4166|title=Catholic Church of Laohukou|last=|first=|date=|website=\u65b0\u7af9\u7e23\u6587\u5316\u5c40|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171027220536/http://www.hchcc.gov.tw/ch/06culture/cul_02_main.asp?bull_id=4166|archive-date=2017-10-27|access-date=}}</ref>[[File:Hukou Sanyuan Temple 20100731.jpg|thumb|Hukou Sanyuan Temple]]\n\n==Transportation==\n\n===Rail===\n[[File:TRA Hukou Station 2013.jpg|thumb|[[Hukou Station]]]]\nThe [[Taiwan Railways Administration]] serves Hukou via the [[Beihu Station|Beihu]] and [[Hukou Station|Hukou]] stations.\n\n===Road===\n[[File:HsinchuBusHukouStation.jpg|thumb|Hukou Bus Station]]\nBus station in the township is Hukou bus station of Hsinchu Bus Corp..\n\n==Notable natives==\n* [[Joe Chen]], actress, singer and television host\n* [[Fan Chen-tsung]], Magistrate of [[Hsinchu County]] (1989-1997)\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Hukou Township, Hsinchu County}}\n* [http://www.hukou.gov.tw/en/index.php Hukou Township Government]\n\n{{Taiwan Hsinchu divisions}}\n{{Townships in Taiwan}}\n\n[[Category:Townships in Hsinchu County]]\n\n\n{{Taiwan-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Kouhu}}\n{{coord|24|54|N|121|03|E|display=title|region:TW_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n{{Short description|rural township of Hsinchu County, Taiwan}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->| official_name                   = Hukou Township<br>\u6e56\u53e3\u9115\n| nickname                        = \n| motto                           = \n| settlement_type                 = [[Township (Taiwan)|Rural township]]\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_flag                      = File:Emblem of hukou township.png\n| image_seal                      = \n| image_map                       = Sj hk.png\n| map_caption                     = Hukou Township in Hsinchu County\n| subdivision_type                = Location\n| subdivision_type1               = \n| subdivision_name                = [[Hsinchu County]], [[Taiwan]]\n| subdivision_name1               = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| established_title2              = \n| established_date2               = \n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = \n| area_total_km2                  = 58.4303\n| area_land_sq_mi                 = \n| area_land_km2                   = \n| area_water_sq_mi                = \n| area_water_km2                  = \n| area_urban_sq_mi                = \n| area_urban_km2                  = \n| area_metro_km2                  = \n| area_metro_sq_mi                =